Development environment installation:

- Install Java

sudo apt install openjdk-8-jdk

- Install JavaFX

sudo apt install openjfx=8u161-b12-1ubuntu2 libopenjfx-java=8u161-b12-1ubuntu2 libopenjfx-jni=8u161-b12-1ubuntu2
sudo apt-mark hold openjfx libopenjfx-java libopenjfx-jni

- Install SBT

echo "deb https://dl.bintray.com/sbt/debian /" | sudo tee -a /etc/apt/sources.list.d/sbt.list
curl -sL "https://keyserver.ubuntu.com/pks/lookup?op=get&search=0x2EE0EA64E40A89B84B2DF73499E82A75642AC823" | sudo apt-key add
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install sbt

- Install IntelliJ or other IDE (optional)

- Math library
Uses math library which is currently not open source. It is build from another project and provided to this project's lib directory.
Math library is build in the application jar and it is part of the deplyment, but not part of the code base.
